{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"fullName":"olivia ifrim","settings":{"disqusShortName":"oliviaifrim","disqusEnabled":false},"twitterHandle":"@oliviff"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"2f3e65e5-ae43-5892-9ee6-c439db7c63ec","html":"<p><a href=\"/posts/design-patterns/\">Previously</a> we discussed design patterns briefly and why you might want to use them, so today we'll continue that journey and look into our first design pattern: the decorator pattern. In this post you are going to learn:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>what is the decorator pattern</li>\n<li>a simple example on how to use it</li>\n<li>advantages and disadvantages of the decorator pattern</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Decorator pattern</h2>\n<p>The decorator pattern is a structural design pattern that allows you to extend the behaviour of an existing class by wrapping it. It's called a decorator because you are decorating the functionality of the initial class.</p>\n<h2>Pizza</h2>\n<p>Everyone loves pizza right? Let's imagine we were writing a recipe website and we wanted to find a good way to manage pizza recipes and especially ingredients. </p>\n<p>So let's write a really simple <code class=\"language-text\">Pizza</code> <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interface_(computing)#In_object-oriented_languages\">interface</a> for that. Quick refresher: an interface defines a behaviour (with no implementation) and a class can choose to implement that interface. So here we are creating a Pizza interface that all Pizza classes will have to implement. </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"typescript\"><pre class=\"language-typescript\"><code class=\"language-typescript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">interface</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Pizza</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token comment\">// Gets all the ingredients of this pizza</span>\n  getIngredients<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token builtin\">string</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Now, let's create a class for the most basic pizza we can think of.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"typescript\"><pre class=\"language-typescript\"><code class=\"language-typescript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">PizzaBase</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">implements</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Pizza</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  getIngredients <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token builtin\">string</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">\"base\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>So what is this doing? We are creating a <code class=\"language-text\">PizzaBase</code> class that implements our <code class=\"language-text\">Pizza</code> interface and returns one single ingredient, the base (or the dough). </p>\n<p>And this is how we would use it.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"typescript\"><pre class=\"language-typescript\"><code class=\"language-typescript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> basicPizza<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> Pizza <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">PizzaBase</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token builtin\">console</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"basic pizza\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token builtin\">console</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>basicPizza<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">getIngredients</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// This will print</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// basic pizza</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// [ 'base' ]</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>Pizza recipes</h3>\n<p>Now, let's say we want to implement two recipies: </p>\n<ol>\n<li>Margheritza (base, tomato and cheese) </li>\n<li>Hawaii (base, tomato, cheese, ham, pineapple) (if you are Italian feel free to skip the pineapple ðŸ˜‚)</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>Basic pizzas</h4>\n<p>Let's do it in the simplest way we can think of, list all the ingredients in each recipe.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"typescript\"><pre class=\"language-typescript\"><code class=\"language-typescript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">MargheritaPizza</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">implements</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Pizza</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  getIngredients <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token builtin\">string</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">\"base\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"tomato\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"cheese\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">HawaiiPizza</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">implements</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Pizza</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  getIngredients <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token builtin\">string</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">\"base\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"tomato\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"cheese\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"ham\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"pineapple\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>And here is how we would use them. </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"typescript\"><pre class=\"language-typescript\"><code class=\"language-typescript\"><span class=\"token comment\">// The margherita</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> margherita<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> Pizza <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">MargheritaPizza</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token builtin\">console</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>margherita<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">getIngredients</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// The Hawaii</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> hawaii<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> Pizza <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">HawaiiPizza</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token builtin\">console</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>hawaii<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">getIngredients</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// This will print</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// [\"base\", \"tomato\", \"cheese\"] // the margherita</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// [\"base\", \"tomato\", \"cheese\", \"ham\", \"pineapple\"] // the hawaii</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Well this is good, it works, but it's not very idiomatic or very extensible. Some of the challenges with this approach are:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>duplication</strong>: every time we want to create a new pizza recipe we need to copy-paste ingredients, that doesn't feel right does it? It's very error prone, we could copy paste wrong and then our front-end would show chiiz instead of ðŸ§€ </li>\n<li><strong>lack of extensibility</strong>: creating a new recipe that has some ingredients (or ingredient combinations we've used before) is the same amount of work as creating a unique recipe, which is also a bad sign because we should be able to re-use the work we've already done. Similarly, if we have a request tomorrow to add deep-dish versions of all these pizzas, there's no easy way for us to use a <code class=\"language-text\">&quot;deepDishBase&quot;</code> to all our recipes.</li>\n<li><strong>not idiomatic</strong>: the code doesn't feel idiomatic, it doesn't feel like we are fully taking advantages of the interface and class constructs (we'll come back to this one shortly). For example, we aren't really taking advantage of the <code class=\"language-text\">PizzaBase</code> class here, even though each of these pizzas does actually have a base. </li>\n</ul>\n<p>So let's see how we can make it better. </p>\n<h4>Decorated pizzas</h4>\n<p>We can use decorators to make our code more idiomatic and extensible. </p>\n<p>A decorator will give us the ability to extend a pizza's recipe with new ingredients. Let's see how that might look like.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"typescript\"><pre class=\"language-typescript\"><code class=\"language-typescript\"><span class=\"token comment\">// We create a class (don't worry about the abstract for now)</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// which implements our interface.</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">abstract</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">PizzaDecorator</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">implements</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Pizza</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">private</span> decoratedPizza<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> Pizza<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token comment\">// We will receive a pizza in our constructor, which we will</span>\n  <span class=\"token comment\">// \"decorate\" with other ingredients. Notice how we keep that </span>\n  <span class=\"token comment\">// object as a member variable.</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">constructor</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>decoratedPizza<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> Pizza<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">this</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>decoratedPizza <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> decoratedPizza<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token comment\">// And lastly, we are implementing the getIngredients methods,</span>\n  <span class=\"token comment\">// but we are just calling our decoratedPizza's getIngredients. </span>\n  <span class=\"token comment\">// We are not adding any new ingredients just yet, we'll come</span>\n  <span class=\"token comment\">// back to that in a second.</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">getIngredients</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token builtin\">string</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">this</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>decoratedPizza<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">getIngredients</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>So now we have a decorator class, <code class=\"language-text\">PizzaDecorator</code>, but on its own that doesn't do anything just yet. <code class=\"language-text\">PizzaDecorator</code> is an abstract class, meaning we can't instantiate it, we can only extend it. So let's create a concrete decorator. </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"typescript\"><pre class=\"language-typescript\"><code class=\"language-typescript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">TomatoCheeseDecorator</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">extends</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">PizzaDecorator</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">getIngredients</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token builtin\">string</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">super</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">getIngredients</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">concat</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">\"tomato\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"cheese\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Now our Margherita would look like this.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"typescript\"><pre class=\"language-typescript\"><code class=\"language-typescript\"><span class=\"token comment\">// The margherita</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> margherita<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> Pizza <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">TomatoCheeseDecorator</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">PizzaBase</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token builtin\">console</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>margherita<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">getIngredients</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// This will print</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// [\"base\", \"tomato\", \"cheese\"]</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Notice how we are getting the same result as in our basic example, but the advantage is that now we can reuse these ingredients in our other recipes. Let's look at what our Hawaii recipe would look like now. </p>\n<p>First we need a decorator for Ham and One for pineapple. </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"typescript\"><pre class=\"language-typescript\"><code class=\"language-typescript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">HamDecorator</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">extends</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">PizzaDecorator</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">getIngredients</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token builtin\">string</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">super</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">getIngredients</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">concat</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"ham\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">PineappleDecorator</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">extends</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">PizzaDecorator</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">getIngredients</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token builtin\">string</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">super</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">getIngredients</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">concat</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"pineapple\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Now back to Hawaii.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"typescript\"><pre class=\"language-typescript\"><code class=\"language-typescript\"><span class=\"token comment\">// The hawaii</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> hawaii<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> Pizza <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">PineappleDecorator</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">HamDecorator</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">TomatoCheeseDecorator</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n      <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">PizzaBase</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token builtin\">console</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>hawaii<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">getIngredients</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// This will print</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// [\"base\", \"tomato\", \"cheese\", \"ham\", \"pineapple\"]</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Going back to the disadvantages of our code before, let's see if this is any better:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>duplication: we are not duplicating ingredients anymore, we are re-using them</li>\n<li>lack of extensibility: now we can easily create new recipies by reusing the ingredients that we've already got, and we cna easily create new ones. What about the deep-dish example? We'll look at that in a second. </li>\n<li>not idiomatic: this code is a lot more idiomatic, we are composing every recipe out of it's own ingredients as opposed to just a flat list. </li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Deep dish pizzas</h4>\n<p>One of the things we couldn't easily do before was go from flat pizza bases to deep dish. But now we can!</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"typescript\"><pre class=\"language-typescript\"><code class=\"language-typescript\"><span class=\"token comment\">// The Hawaii</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> hawaii<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> Pizza <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">PineappleDecorator</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">HamDecorator</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">TomatoCheeseDecorator</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n      <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">PizzaBase</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token builtin\">console</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"hawaii pizza\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token builtin\">console</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>hawaii<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">getIngredients</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// The Hawaii deep dish</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> deepDishHawaii<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> Pizza <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">PineappleDecorator</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">HamDecorator</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">TomatoCheeseDecorator</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n      <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">DeepDishPizzaBase</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token builtin\">console</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"deep dish hawaii pizza\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token builtin\">console</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>deepDishHawaii<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">getIngredients</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// This will print </span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// </span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// hawaii pizza</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// [ 'base', 'tomato', 'cheese', 'ham', 'pineapple' ]</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// </span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// deep dish hawaii pizza</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// [ 'deepDishBase', 'tomato', 'cheese', 'ham', 'pineapple' ]</span></code></pre></div>\n<h2>Wrapping up</h2>\n<p>So in short, the decorator pattern is used when you want to reuse some existing functionality and augment/extend it in some way.</p>\n<p><strong>Advantages</strong>:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>no code duplication - we don't need to copy paste anything, we just re-used the rot13 and caesar implementations we already had</li>\n<li>makes it easy to combine existing functionality in new ways</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Disadvantages</strong>:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>more boilerplate structural code</li>\n<li>code can get more complex if decorators use decorators which use decorators</li>\n</ul>\n<p>So do you always need to use decorators? No, you can use them when you have a problem which lends itself to the pattern (which is largely the case for all design patterns). No pattern is a silver bullet to all problems, it's just a potential solution to a part of the problem. </p>\n<p>Have you used the decorator pattern recently? Have you thought of a usecase now that you've read this post? Let me know!</p>","excerpt":"Previously  we discussed design patterns briefly and why you might want to use them, so today we'll continue that journey and look into ourâ€¦","frontmatter":{"title":"What do pizzas and decorators have in common?","date":"January 13, 2019","tags":["design patterns","design","decorator pattern"],"featuredImage":{"childImageSharp":{"sizes":{"src":"/static/d8829f32c0b6806994b03e4a3132cedf/5aa81/pizza.jpg","srcSet":"/static/d8829f32c0b6806994b03e4a3132cedf/25db0/pizza.jpg 175w,\n/static/d8829f32c0b6806994b03e4a3132cedf/62b24/pizza.jpg 350w,\n/static/d8829f32c0b6806994b03e4a3132cedf/5aa81/pizza.jpg 700w,\n/static/d8829f32c0b6806994b03e4a3132cedf/6d6c4/pizza.jpg 800w","base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":2.3333333333333335,"sizes":"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px"}}}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/decorator-pattern-ciphers/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/posts/design-patterns/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Design patterns"}},"next":null}}